<p><a href="#sdfootnote6anc" name="sdfootnote6sym">6</a> Adrienne Rich, “Notes Towards the Politics of Location,”<em> </em>in: <em>Blood, Bread, and Poetry: Selected Prose 1979-1985</em> (New York: W. W. Norton &amp; Company, 1984), 212.</p>
<p><a href="#sdfootnote7anc" name="sdfootnote7sym">7</a> Adrienne Rich, “When We Dead Awaken: Writing as Re-Vision,” in: <em>On Lies, Secrets, and Silence: Selected Prose 1966-1978</em> (New York: W. W. Norton &amp; Company, 1979), 35. Quoted in: Felman, <em>What Does a Woman Want?</em>, 13.</p>
