<p><a href="#sdfootnote15anc" name="sdfootnote15sym">15</a> It was in the same year, 1980, that Lassnig, together with VALIE EXPORT, represented Austria at the Venice Biennale; two years later, in 1982, she participated in <em>documenta 7</em>, and in 1997 in <em>documenta 10</em>. At the Venice Biennale in 2013 she received, together with another female artist, Marisa Merz, the Golden Lion for Lifetime Achievement.</p>
